---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="How to Count Tiles in Scrabble — Tile Tracking Guide" description="Master tile tracking in Scrabble: count what's been played, calculate what remains in the bag, and deduce your opponent's rack for strategic advantage." keywords="scrabble tile tracking, count tiles scrabble, tile counting strategy, what tiles are left scrabble, deduce opponent rack, scrabble tile distribution">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"How to Count Tiles in Scrabble — Tile Tracking Guide","description":"Master tile tracking: count played tiles, calculate remaining distribution, and deduce opponent racks.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/how-to-count-tiles-scrabble"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you track tiles in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Keep a reference sheet with all 100 tiles listed. Cross off each letter as it's played on the board. At any point, uncrossed letters minus your rack = what's in the bag + opponent's rack. This gets more precise as the game progresses."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is tile tracking allowed in tournament Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — tile tracking is completely legal and expected in competitive play. Players use a pre-printed tracking sheet showing all tile distributions. It's considered a fundamental skill, not cheating."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When should you start counting tiles?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Start from the first move. Track every tile played on the board throughout the game. The information becomes most valuable in the midgame (when you can predict likely draws) and critical in the endgame (when you can deduce exact opponent tiles)."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12"><article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span></nav>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">How to Count Tiles in Scrabble — Tile Tracking Guide</h1>
    <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>6 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Tile tracking is the single biggest skill gap between casual and competitive Scrabble players. Knowing what's left in the bag transforms guesswork into calculation. By the endgame, you can deduce your opponent's exact rack — and plan accordingly.</p>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center"><div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">100</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Total Tiles</p></div><div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">27</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Unique Letters</p></div><div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Blank Tiles</p></div><div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E Tiles (most)</p></div></div></div>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What's Been Played</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use a tracking sheet:</span> Print the full tile distribution (A×9, B×2, C×2... Z×1, Blank×2). Cross off each letter as it appears on the board. This takes 2 seconds per turn and gives enormous advantage.</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Track high-value first:</span> If you can't track everything, focus on Q, Z, X, J, blanks, and S tiles. Knowing whether Q is still in the bag changes your strategy dramatically.</p></div>
    </div>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Remains in the Bag</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">The formula:</span> Remaining = Total distribution - Board tiles - Your rack. If 3 of 9 A's are on the board and you hold 1, there are 5 A's between the bag and opponent's rack.</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Draw probability:</span> Knowing the bag composition helps you decide whether to exchange. If 8 of 12 E's are gone and you need vowels, the bag is vowel-poor — exchanging might not help.</p></div>
    </div>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Deducing Opponent's Rack</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Empty bag = perfect info</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">100 - board - your rack = their exact tiles</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Watch their exchanges</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">If they exchange 4 tiles, they likely had vowel/consonant imbalance</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Block accordingly</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">If they hold Q with no U on board, block QI spots</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Predict their moves</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Knowing their tiles means knowing their best possible plays</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20"><p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p><p class="text-base text-gray-200">Tile tracking isn't optional at the competitive level — <span class="text-white font-medium">every tournament player does it</span>. Start with just tracking the power tiles (Q, Z, X, J, S, blanks) and build up to full tracking as it becomes habit.</p></div>
    <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose"><h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3><div class="grid gap-3"><a href="/blog/scrabble-endgame-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Endgame Strategy</span></a><a href="/blog/tile-tracking-guide/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Tile Tracking Guide — Advanced Techniques</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-tile-tracking-methods/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Tile Tracking Methods in Scrabble</span></a>
</div></aside>
    <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl"><div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap"><p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Track tiles with our probability panel — free Scrabble solver</p><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a></div></div>
    <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
  </article></div>
</BlogLayout>
